dbStoredQuestions.questionText: Find the greatest common factor and least common multiple of two whole numbers less than or equal to 100 using prime factorization and related strategies.

standards.description: Find the greatest common factor and least common multiple of two whole numbers less than or equal to 100 using prime factorization and related strategies.
standards.subject: Mathematics

rigor.justification: The tasks are predominantly procedural and computational (prime factorization, integer addition/subtraction/multiplication/division, order of operations, graphing on a number line and writing inequalities). They require application of algorithms and multi-step computation rather than simple recall or deep multi-step reasoning/proof.

dbStoredQuestions.questionText: Apply and extend previous understandings of addition and subtraction to add and subtract rational numbers; represent addition and subtraction on a horizontal or vertical number line; use ordering of rational numbers and represent comparisons with inequalities.
